pip install Django
	// This command installed the framework that is Django. 

pip list
	//This command shows the list of installed packages in column formatting

pip install Django 
	//returns information that Django is already installed. 

pip freeze 
	//This command shows the list of packages in the requirements formats...details the version tyo that must be installed to run. difference: Freeze lets you know where you should be as opposed to the list detailing where you are. 

pip freeze > requirements.txt. 
	// This command creates a document detailing the required packages. WHen you ls you see the created files and the content is whats listed above.


pip uninstall Django
	//uninstalls previously installed package.


pip show Django
	//Shows the version of the package that is currently installed.


pip search Flask
	//shows list of flask packages that could potentially be installed.



